Blake: I'm just trying to stop you from destroying our son's life. Alexis: I am his mother, I know what's good for him. Blake: No, you're using him for your stupid games against me. I can run, walk fast, cycle, kayak, swim anything really, aur ye saare activites mere liye ache hai, pr khade rhna ,abhi tk ek bada issue hai.  Micky:Tum hr din bina khadi hui kaise manage krti ho?! Kate: Help me! Kate: Mera computer crash hogaya hai Kate: Main kuch nahi kar sakti aur mera unsaved project hai jo main loose nahi karna chahti Kate: Merko restart nahi karna Bill: Easy. Pehle cad banate hai Kate: Kya? Bill: Press CTRL, ALT aur DELETE same time pe Kate: Task manager aa gaya Bill: Dekho kaunse application ke paas "not responding" clause hai Kate: Microsoft Word Bill: Dhundho option close karne ka word task manager mein Bill: agar ye help nahi karega tum shut kar sakti ho all opened apps Bill: afar app close nahi hoga try to switch column to processes aur shut down process corresponding with app.  Bill: For example word is WINWORD.exe -  tumhare paas description hai to the right Kate: Ok. It works Bill: great! Bill: Yaad rakhna apne projects save karna regularly. Kate: Thank you :*

Frannie: Hi Jim Jim: Oh, hi Fran Frannie: lagta hai tumbhi mere jaisa kal ke exam ke liye dare hue ho Jim: mujhe bhi lagta hai Frannie: mujhe substrata aur superstrata wala part samajh nahi aaya Jim: easy hai actually aur uska ek achha Wikipedia page bhi hai XD Frannie: mujhe Wiki se zyada tumhare notes par bharosa hai Jim: And rightly so! Anyway Frannie: mai sunn rahi hu (ya padh rahi hu) Jim: substratum ya substrate essentially ek language hai jo ek given territory m thi koi aur language aane ke pehle Frannie: Ok Jim: phir uss territory mai alag languages bolne waale log aa gaye aur dheere dheere unki language dominant ban gayi Frannie: aur purani language naye wale ko influence karti hai na? Jim: haa.substratum dheere dheere khatam ho jaati hai par naye language (the superstratum) mai kuch parts chhor jaati hai jaise words, pronunciation aspects and so on Frannie: Ok, example ke liye the Etruscan language substratum thi aur Latin superstratum, na? Jim: Haa, aur Etruscan ne local variety latin ko influence kiya tha later centuries mai Frannie: Ok Jim: mujhe bhi ek sawal hai Frannie: Tum? mujhe laga tum Mr. Perfect Notes ho Jim: hu par , maine November mai 2 lessons miss kiye the Frannie: Ok Jim: to... "Mediolanum" naam ki story hai ? Frannie: Ok, ye wala mujhe aata hai. ancient Celtic languages mai Indoeuropean consonant "p" pronounce nahi hota tha, for example "father" ke liye "athir" (vs. "pater" Latin mai for example). kaafi scholars ke hisab se "Mediolanum" "medio-" aur "planum" se aaya kyuki koi "p" nahi hai, so it's basically "in the middle of the plane". Jim: Ok! Thanks Frannie: You're more than welcome, tumne bhi mere madad ki Jim: ;) Frannie: Good luck kal ke liye! Jim: Godspeed!

Rob: The meniscus is the soft cartilage between your knees. Actually, we have 2 of them. Well, one of mine is damaged and needs to be removed. Gina: Have you signed up for surgery? Rob: No, not yet. I checked out 1 hospital and they told me the earliest date they have available is in the year 2022...hehe. Gina: What? Are you serious?? Rob: Yeah, I know, it's crazy. I'm thinking of going privately. Gina: How much would it be privately?  Rob: 5000 Gina: That's not too bad. I mean, it's a lot, but not outrageous. Rob: Yeah, I know. Plus I can always get a small loan and pay it off slowly. Gina: Better than waiting till 2022. Is it painful? Rob: I have no idea. It would be arthroscopic surgery, so it's minimally invasive, I guess. Gina: Ok, that's not too bad. My uncle's had arthroscopy done. He was out and about 2 days after he got out of the hospital. Rob: Hmm... that doesn't sound too bad. I've read a lot of blogs on it. Everyone says something different. Gina: I don't think you should worry too much about it. What can happen if you don't do anything? Rob: Well, it could get a lot worse, damaging other parts of the knee. Plus I avoid certain movements now. I'm afraid of the knee locking up, and that's PAINFUL! Gina: That's not good. Just sign up for the surgery. I can help you out a little with the cost. Rob: It's ok, don't worry. I'll go to the bank and get a loan. Gina: The interest's going to be high. If I lend you a little, you won't have to borrow that much. Rob: That's really nice of you. I'll think about it. John: Mera budget kaafi limited hai waisi hi meri  living room mein space… Michael: main advise karunga ki you first measure the room taaki pata chale ki machine kitni badi ho sakti hai ki tum comfortably aur effectively exercise kar pao Tom: Waste of money, most expensive cloth hanger John: Hahaha, mere case mein na ho. Michael: You can always exercise with your phone and an app, but ye most comfortable way nahi hai (tried it myself). It’s good to have kam se kam three preinstalled programmes like weight-loss, interval, etc. Then the machine will think for you. Anna: Mere first cross trainer mein ye options nahi the and I must admit that I was also training with my phone and keeping my times. Now, when the old broke, maine “fancier” model khareeda and I definitely don’t regret it John: Koi company hai that you can recommend? Ya koi specific model? Susan: I have OBE8731 Powerstride 18" Rear Drive and I think it’s ok. Anna: I think that in case of cross trainer it really goes down to the price range. tum bauhat acchi equipment cheaply nahi le paoge Michael: I agree, especially if you’re determined and interested in your scores. I can’t spend too much, but main apna money kisi aesi cheez pe nahi throw karna chahta that won’t serve me… Anna: Sure, again, in my opinion it is a thing worth investing in.
